ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great insight into the current state of biomaterials and how they interact with tissues. Compelling lectures that are truly worth attending, and you can learn really interesting things without a lot of busy work to bog you down.
I would definitely recommend this class as it sets you up with an excellent understanding of the tissue engineering field.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course built very well on the biomaterials course I took in the fall, and presented very important questions that will be crucial to keep in mind as I continue to work on my thesis.
This course left me very interested in thinking about and developing coatings for biologic devices that could be used as brain / spinal cord implants during surgery.
